						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar built into the Peddāpuram gate in the Missionary's compound.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1133, Akshaya-tṛitīyā, Thursday.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of five <hi rend="italic">madas</hi> for burning two perpetual lamps to the god Sōmēśvara of Tilavyāva-tirtha by Valyāsāni daughter of Kāmi-seṭṭi.</p>						

